<title>FRANCE: Remy Cointreau year sales up 4.8 pct.</title>
<headline>Remy Cointreau year sales up 4.8 pct.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-05-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year to March 31, 1997.</p>
<p>(All figures in millions of French francs)</p>
<p>Total sales		 7.132    vs     6.802</p>
<p>     -- Cognac		   2.322    vs     2.386</p>
<p>     -- Wines and Spirits    2.251    vs     2.122</p>
<p>     -- Champagne		  900    vs	 889</p>
<p>     -- Partner brands	 1.658    vs     1.406</p>
<p>NOTE - Remy Cointreau said in a statement that it had during the year taken measures to boost its brands which should help results in 1997/1998. It said Remy Martin cognac sales were slightly down in Japan and Thailand. Sales at Piper-Heidsieck, Charles Heisieck and Krug champagnes were up 10 percent.</p>
</text>
